%N A396864 Discriminants of real quadratic fields K such that Po(K) != Cl(K), where Po(K) is the Pólya group and Cl(K) is the class group of K.
%C A396864 The Pólya group Po(K) of a number field K is the subgroup of class group Cl(K) generated by {products of prime ideals of O_K with norm q : q prime powers}. For K being a quadratic field, it is clear that Po(K) is generated by prime ideals lying above each ramified prime, and Po(K) is an elementary abelian 2-group.
%C A396864 Let Cl+(K) be the form class group of the real quadratic field K of discriminant D. We have:
%C A396864 I. If D has a prime factor congruent to 3 modulo 4, then Po(K) and Cl(K) have the same 2-rank (omega(D) - 2, omega = A001221), and Cl+(K) = Cl(K) X C_2;
%C A396864 II. If D has no prime factor congruent to 3 modulo 4, and the fundamental unit has norm 1, then the 2-ranks of Po(K) and Cl(K) are different, so Po(K) != Cl(K). Note that in this case Cl(K) and Cl+(K) have the same 2-rank (omega(D) - 1), so Cl+(K) contains C_4 as a subgroup;
%C A396864 III. If D has no prime factor congruent to 3 modulo 4, and the fundamental unit has norm -1, then Po(K) and Cl(K) have the same 2-rank (omega(D) - 1, omega = A001221), and Cl+(K) = Cl(K).
%C A396864 Since Po(K) = Cl(K) if and only if Cl(K) is an elementary abelian 2-group having the same 2-rank of Po(K), we have that Po(K) = Cl(K) if and only if Cl+(K) is an elementary abelian 2-group. So this sequence lists discriminants of real quadratic fields whose *form class group* is not isomorphic to (C_2)^r, r >= 0.
%C A396864 Complement of A391422 with respect to A003658.
%H A396864 Jianing Song, <a href="/A396864/b396864.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A396864 Jean-Luc Chabert, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jnt.2019.03.008">From Pólya fields to Pólya groups (I) Galois extensions</a>, Journal of Number Theory, 2019, 203, pp.360-375.
%o A396864 (PARI) isA396864(n)={n>1 && isfundamental(n) && #select(k->k<>2, bnfnarrow(bnfinit(X^2-n)).cyc)}
%Y A396864 Cf. A003658, A003652 (class groups), A396866 (Pólya groups), A391422.
%Y A396864 Different 2-ranks related to real quadratic fields: A317991 (form class groups), A391436 (class groups), A396865 (Pólya groups).
